   <head>EPITAPH ON CLAUDIUS PHILLIPS.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">PHILLIPS! whose touch harmonious could remove</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">The pangs of guiltless power or hapless love,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Rest here oppress'd by poverty no more,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Here find that calm thou gav'st so oft before:</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Rest undisturb'd within this humble shrine,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Till angels wake thee with a note like thine.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
